5|$|Most current {{scholars}} {{consider the}} Codex Vaticanus {{to be one}} of the best Greek texts of the <b>New</b> <b>Testament,</b> with the Codex Sinaiticus as its only competitor. Until the discovery by Tischendorf of the Sinaiticus text, the Codex was unrivaled. It was extensively used by Westcott and Hort in their edition of The <b>New</b> <b>Testament</b> in the Original Greek in 1881. The most widely sold editions of the Greek <b>New</b> <b>Testament</b> are largely based on the text of the Codex Vaticanus.|$|E
