5|$|In 1868–1881 C. Vercellone, Giuseppe Cozza-Luzi, and G. Sergio {{published}} an {{edition of the}} entire codex in 6 volumes (<b>New</b> <b>Testament</b> in volume V; Prolegomena in volume VI). A typographical facsimile appeared between 1868 and 1872. In 1889–1890 a photographic facsimile of the entire manuscript was made and published by Cozza-Luzi, in three volumes. Another facsimile of the <b>New</b> <b>Testament</b> text was published in 1904–1907 in Milan. As a result, the Codex became widely available.|$|E
